╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
║  HELIX TRAINER — Exercise 3.3: Undo, Redo, and Repeat           ║
║  Category: Changes               Difficulty: ★☆☆ Fundamental    ║
╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝

COMMANDS TO LEARN
─────────────────
  u     Undo
  U     Redo
  .     Repeat last insert/change

NOTE: Helix uses U for redo (not Ctrl-r like Vim).
      Zed also supports Ctrl-r as a non-standard extra.

INSTRUCTIONS
────────────
  Transform each line by adding the prefix "DONE: " before it.

  Efficient strategy using repeat (.):
  1. Go to the first line
  2. Press g h to go to line start (or I to insert at start)
  3. Type "DONE: " then Esc
  4. Move to the next line
  5. Press . to repeat the insertion
  6. Repeat for all lines

  If you make a mistake, press u to undo!

────────────────────────── PRACTICE ──────────────────────────────

Buy groceries
Walk the dog
Write code
Read a book

────────────────────────── EXPECTED ──────────────────────────────

DONE: Buy groceries
DONE: Walk the dog
DONE: Write code
DONE: Read a book

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
HINTS (read only if stuck):
  Hint 1: On "Buy groceries", press I to enter insert mode at
          line start. Type "DONE: " then Esc.
  Hint 2: Press j to move down, then . to repeat.
  Hint 3: The . command repeats your last insert — the "DONE: "
          text gets inserted at the cursor position.
  Hint 4: If . inserts in the wrong place, try I then Esc first
          to position correctly, then . on subsequent lines.
